      "caption": "Delta Channels: How We\u2019re Evolving our Runtime for Long-Running Agents\n\nLong-running agents have a storage problem: checkpointing full state at every step grows at O(N\u00b2). DeltaChannel is a new primitive in LangGraph 1.2 that checkpoints only the diff each step and writes full snapshots periodically, keeping storage costs flat as sessions grow longer. It ships by default in Deep Agents v0.6, with no config changes or data migration required.\n\nCovered from 5 linked story/stories in this email.\n\nQuick takeaways:\n- Tracks 5 new launches AI launch activity from LangChain Blog, MIT Tech Review AI.\n- Best posting angle: explain what changed, who it helps, and why creators should care.\n- Primary entities to watch: OpenAI, Google, GPT-3, claude-code.\n- Likely content themes: model release, funding or business, regulation or safety.\n\nDisclaimer: This post is an AI-assisted news summary. Check the linked source before making business, legal, or investment decisions.\n\n#Openai #Google #Anthropic #Microsoft #Tesla #Xai #AiLab #TargetingAi #Gpt3 #ClaudeCode #Claude #Grok #ModelRelease #FundingOrBusiness #RegulationOrSafety #DeveloperTools\n",
